\section{Self-consistent Cluster Mean Field Approximation}

In this section, we explain how the effective model in terms of pinwheel densities as given in Eq.\ \eqref{eq:pwham} can be improved using a cluster mean field approach. 

Let $\mathcal{P} = \{P_1, P_2, \dots \}$ denote the set of pinwheel structures in a certain crystal structure. The full crystal Hamiltonian which only neglects kinetic processes between dimers of different pinwheel structures then reads

text:
\begin{equation}
 \mathcal{H}_{\rm c}= \sum_{i} \mathcal{H}_{\text{eff}}^{(i)} + \frac{1}{2} \sum_{\substack{i,j\\i\neq j}} \sum_{\substack{k\in P_i\\ l \in P_j}} V_{kl}\, \hat{n}_k \hat{n}_l 
\label{eq:crystham}
\end{equation}
